Pour the @Water{300%ml} for the rice (see pantry for amount) into a #medium saucepan{} with a tight-fitting #lid{}. Stir in the @Basmati Rice{150%g} and @salt{1/4%tsp} and bring to the boil. Once boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a #large frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Add the @Diced Chicken Thigh{260%g} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Fry until browned all over, ~{5-6%minutes}. Turn occasionally.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

While the chicken cooks, halve the @Green Pepper{1}(halved) and discard the core and seeds. Chop into 2cm chunks. Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Once the chicken has browned, add the pepper to the pan and cook until starting to soften, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir in the garlic and @Rogan Josh Curry Paste{50%g} and cook for ~{1% minute} more, then stir in the @Tomato Passata{1%100ml carton}, @Chicken Stock Paste{10%g} and @Water{100%ml} for the curry (see pantry for amount).

Bring the curry to a boil, then lower the heat and simmer until the chicken is cooked through and the sauce has thickened, ~{10-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once cooked, taste the curry and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add some @?Chilli Flakes{1%pinch} if you'd like some more heat (careful, they're hot), then stir through the @Mango Chutney{40%g}.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{}, then share between your bowls.

Top with the chicken rogan josh and sprinkle with the @Toasted Flaked Almonds{15%g} to finish. Enjoy!